    "body": "Le 13 janv. 2013 à 11:41, Honghe a écrit :\n\n> enviroment:\n> \n>   • Windows 7 32bit English\n>   • IPython 0.13.1\n>   • Sublime Text 2.0.1 I set $EDITOR to Sublime Text 2.\n> And when apply %ed or %edit to edit some code in Sublime Text,\n> I have to close/exit Sublime Text, i.e. to close all the tabs in Sublime Text.\n> It is very inconvenient, when I use Sublime to edit some other stuff.\n> So can IPython be triggered just by close the file/tab opened by %edit magic?\n\nIf the call to the program you use is blocking no. \nbut looking at the %edit? help you see that you can use -x flag not to execute on return and change the call line to invoke Sublime\nnot  to block. \n\n## This way you can do %edit to edit a file and run it with %run.\n\nMatthias\n"
  },
