    "body": "Le 13 janv. 2013 à 13:03, Honghe a écrit :\n\n> @Carreau but in this way (%edit -x) will raise another problem if I just %edit a temporary code file/snippet.\n> when save and close the temp file, and back to IPython, it will raise a warning, and lost the code:\n> \n> WARNING: File not found. Did you forget to save?\n> \n> The way you suggested (%edit -x and the %run) will be effective only in situation of a specified file.\n\nWith editing the current snippet, the event loop is blocked and the result executed only once it resume. \nHence once the the editor is closed. \n\nIf you want a deeper integration there is nothing that can be done from within IPython.\nYou wil have to configure your editor to 'talk' to IPython. And that will probably be possible only\nwith zmq-console/qtconsole/notebook\n\n## \n\nMatthias\n"
